data.chText: 小规模战斗；小冲突；（尤指）遭遇战
data.enText: a short fight between small groups of soldiers, etc., especially one that is not planned

data.chText: （尤指政治上对立双方的）小争执，小争论
data.enText: a short argument, especially between political opponents

data.chText: 发生小规模战斗（或冲突、争执）
data.enText: to take part in a short fight or argument

data.chText: 有报道称在边界一带发生了小规模冲突。
data.enText: There are reports of skirmishing along the border.

means: (尤指政治上对立双方的)小争执，小争论
发生小规模战斗(或冲突、争执)

example.ex: Border skirmishes between India and Pakistan were common.
example.tran: 印度和巴基斯坦边境上常常发生小规模战斗。

example.ex: They were skirmishing close to the minefield now...
example.tran: 他们当时正在雷区附近交火。

example.ex: Police skirmished with youths on the estate last Friday.
example.tran: 上周五警方与一些青年在住宅区发生了冲突。

value.tran: 发生小冲突;进行小规模战斗;打斗

example.ex: On land there was minor skirmishing.
example.tran: 陆地上发生了小规模的战斗。

value.def: A skirmish is a short, sharp argument.

example.ex: This difference in approach has led to several political skirmishes.
example.tran: 这种方式上的差异已经导致了几场政治冲突。
